&nbsp; 
 &nbsp; 
   The article presents a comprehensive analysis of the current state of the problem of ixodid tick-borne borreliosis (Lyme disease) in Ukraine [1, 14]. The dynamics of incidence, driven by climate change and ecological transformations that contribute to the expansion of vector habitats, are considered [7, 22]. Special attention is paid to the clinical diversity of the disease course, including anerythematous forms and systemic lesions in late stages [3, 19]. In the context of diagnosis, the role of polymerase chain reaction (PCR) as a technological breakthrough that allows for pathogen verification at early stages is analyzed [2, 18, 30].    
 &nbsp;

